					<description><![CDATA[<p>Kling AI just closed a massive funding round. The generative AI video platform announced it has raised over 19 billion yuan from external backers. That translates to roughly $2.8 billion</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/kling-ai-raises-2-8-billion-with-alibaba-backing/" data-wpel-link="internal">Kling AI Raises $2.8 Billion in $18 Billion Valuation Backed By Alibaba &amp; Tencent</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kling AI just closed a massive funding round. The generative AI video platform announced it has </span><a href="https://www1.hkexnews.hk/listedco/listconews/sehk/2026/0702/2026070204065.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">raised</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> over 19 billion yuan from external backers. That translates to roughly $2.8 billion in fresh capital. Kling AI raises $2.8 billion at a $15 billion valuation on a pre-money basis.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Once the remaining investors join within two months, the post-money valuation will hit $18 billion. This is the largest funding round ever completed by an AI video model developer globally. Parent company Kuaishou Technology disclosed the financing in a Hong Kong exchange filing. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The capital injection officially launches Kling AI as an independent entity. This money will fund rapid expansion and expensive infrastructure. The company will hire top-tier research talent globally.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Tech Heavyweights Join Forces</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203337" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203337" class="size-large wp-image-203337" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Kling-AI-1024x582.jpg" alt="A green and black image with the Kling AI logo centralized in the middle" width="1024" height="582" /><p id="caption-attachment-203337" class="wp-caption-text">Kling AI Logo</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investor roster backing Kling AI’s latest funding round reads like a roll call of Chinese tech giants. Industry rivals Alibaba and Tencent both agreed to take stakes in the startup. Search leader Baidu also joined the mega-round alongside them. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Financial institutions co-led the deal, including BlueFive Capital, CPE Yuanfeng, and CITIC Securities. Dozens of state-backed funds and commercial banks participated as well. Tencent notably contributed $200 million to the deal. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This strategic move turned heads because Tencent already operates one of the </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/best-free-ai-video-generators/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">best AI video generators</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> called Hunyuan. This corporate cross-investment shows massive local conviction in Kling’s market traction. No major platform wants to be left out of this boom.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/aligned-raises-60m-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Aligned Closes $60M Series B to Solidify Position in B2B Sales</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Kling AI is Stepping Into the Global Void</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The timing of this funding round is highly strategic. It arrives just as Western competition begins to cool down. OpenAI completely shut down the consumer version of its Sora app in April 2026. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">High computing costs and low monetization forced their sudden exit. Runway also shifted focus away from commercial consumer video tools. This has left the global market wide open for a well-capitalized alternative. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kling AI is stepping directly into this void. The company is positioning itself to capture global market share. American tech giants are currently rethinking their consumer video infrastructure strategies.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/twelvelabs-raises-100m-series-b-to-advance-video-intelligence/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>TwelveLabs Raises $100M Series B to Advance Video Intelligence</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Explosive Revenue and Commercial Growth</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In contrast to many AI startups that throw away money on a poorly designed demo reel, Kling AI is generating revenue. Its operations are growing at an astounding rate. Its </span><a href="https://www.moomoo.com/news/post/70627875/kling-ai-s-annualized-arr-approaches-usd-500-million-kuaishou?level=1&amp;data_ticket=1783098927417682" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">first quarter revenue</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for 2026 also exceeded 650 million yuan ($96 million). </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This is a huge 300% increase from last year. Additionally, its revenue run rate is about $500 million annually in March. That’s a big increase from $300 million two months ago in January. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The explosive growth that followed was a result of the rollout of Kling 3.0 upgrade. The system provides amazing 4K video clips based on text prompts. It’s rapidly gaining traction in the film, ad and online worlds. The number of users grows by the day, and they are not just limited to any particular market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kuaishou’s AI business is rapidly expanding, with long-term ambitions to be ambitious. This huge infusion of capital makes a corporate spin-off an obvious starting point. Following the cash injection, Kuaishou will dilute its ownership stake down to about 68%.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Insiders report that Kuaishou intends to initiate a public listing process for Kling AI very soon. The company is targetting a high-profile Hong Kong IPO by mid-2027. Proceeds from the upcoming public offering will directly finance data center expansion and advanced hardware acquisition.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/raja-koduri-oxmiq-raises-35m-license-ai-chips/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Raja Koduri’s OXMIQ Raises $35M To License AI Chips</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/kling-ai-raises-2-8-billion-with-alibaba-backing/" data-wpel-link="internal">Kling AI Raises $2.8 Billion in $18 Billion Valuation Backed By Alibaba &amp; Tencent</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
